Author: Leigh Bardugo
My Review:
The book literally devoured me.

Honestly I had no high hopes of liking this book even though it was very very hyped but later on I thought to give it a chance. After rereading the first few pages for 4/5th time since 2020 and failing miserably to continue the book, I decided to buy the hardcopy (very smart of me). Little did I know it was one of the best decisions that I had ever taken.

I would highly agree that the initial first 100 pages were slow and most of time I was pretty clueless with what's going on. The world also seemed hard to understand as well as the characters. However, the story really picked up from the middle and it didn't stop. This is a book which makes you stay awake 5am in the morning. Eventually I came to love all the characters, specially Alex , Dawes , Turner and DARLINGTON.

At first, I thought of giving it a 4 out of 5 stars but the final 100 pages made up for everything and it truly deserves a 5⭐.
